The paper deals with phase retrieval, which is a problem in signal processing and imaging. The paper specifically focuses on the uniqueness conditions for sparse signals, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of compressed sensing (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions applications in imaging and optics, which suggests that it could also fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also uses combinatorial methods to analyze the problem, which could place it in the subfield of numerical analysis (cs.NA) or discrete mathematics (cs.DS).
